CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, June 10, 1961, pg. A10 reads: "At Grand Master's Banquet - The above group got together for this picture at the Grand Master's Banquet, last Saturday night, at the Hotel Penn-Sheraton, where the state meeting of Prince Hall Masons' Grand Lodge was in session. Left to right: seated: Mrs. Mary C. Johnson of Harrisburg; Mrs. Samuel Daniels, Baltimore, Md.; Mrs. Ruth Tucker, Pittsburgh, Grand Worthy Matron, OES, PHA; and Mrs. A. William Hill Jr. of Philadelphia.  Back row: Mrs. Edgar C. Patience, Wilkes-Barre; A. William Hill Jr., Philadelphia, Grand Master PHA; Mrs. Major A. Green, Wilkinsburg, and Mrs. B.M. Owens, Shippensburg. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait from left, seated: Mary C. Johnson, Mrs. Samuel Daniels, Ruth Tucker, and Mrs. A. William Hill Jr.; back row: Mrs. Edgar C. Patience, A. William Hill Jr., Mrs. Major A. Green, and Mrs. B.M. Owens, gathered at long banquet table, for Prince Hall Masons' Grand Lodge Grand Master's Banquet in the Penn Sheraton Hotel
